VALUES ('Memories from a Sinking Ship: A Novel', 'Juan', '2588149999540', '80', 'Winner of the 2007 Christopher Isherwood Foundation Award for FictionReminiscent of Mark Twains Huckleberry Finn and Ernest Hemingways Nick Adams stories, Memories from a Sinking Ship travels the landscape of a turbulent world seen through a boy’s steady gaze. Like Twain’s Mississippi River and Hemingway’s Big Two-Hearted, Gifford’s Chicago, New Orleans, and the highways and byways between offer us mesmerizing lives lost in the kaleidoscope of postwar America, in particular those of Roy’s adrift and disappointed mother and his hoodlum father.', 7, 'https://books.google.gr/books/content?id=G72Oa1hjqbEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&imgtk=AFLRE71PyfZiaXSYo32oj7-hwlCKPYmQaRoifH91D5IuEWrizlGYTpSVpFz1eOssJNFeC74ZoWD0yfc5yr5gqmC0srVCPppCI6hec_OiPMUcN7zruSBcOFNPYPqpJxv9zrxLFDM3q4mG', 'English','father.');
